            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Confirmed by these steps:\r\n\r\n1. start a tcp server as described at `:help tcp-server`\r\n2. `lua =vim.lsp.rpc.connect('localhost', 57945)()` fails\r\n    ```\r\n    E5108: ... lsp/rpc.lua:706: Invalid IP address or port [localhost:57945]\r\n    ```\r\n3. `lua =vim.lsp.rpc.connect('0.0.0.0', 57945)()` returns an object (doesn't fail)\r\n\r\nIn fact, it's not necessary to start a TCP server. It seems that the \"Invalid IP address or port\" message is coming from a validation step.\r\n\r\n> I would be happy to either PR functionality for DNS lookup, or a documentation change to make this clearer depending on what the correct direction should be\r\n\r\nFor now we should document it.",
